To investigate the practicability of the proposed method, three concentration of cucumin (5.04, 10.08 and 15.12 μg/mL) were spiked to the ginger juice, resulting in the recovery rates ranging from 101.47 % to 103.94 (R < 5 %), as shown in Table 1
                        . Therefore, the analyzed method possesses high reproducibility, accuracy and cost efficiency. Compared with other methods, this work can provide preferable detection performance with a wide linear range and low LOD (Table 2
                        ).
